    <h1>Propositions and reports</h1>
  
  </div></div>
  

  <div class="documentBody" id="Tekstinnhold">   
  <div>
    <p>
</p><table width="100%" border="0">
<tbody>
<tr valign="top">
<td>
<h3>Propositions to the Storting</h3>
<p><strong>"Stortingsproposisjoner (St.prp.)" <br /></strong>are bills inviting the Storting to pass non-legislative resolutions, i.e. concerning fiscal or other matters. Such bills are being handled in plenary sessions of the Storting.</p>
<p><strong>"Odelstingsproposisjoner (Ot.prp.)" <br /></strong>are legislative bills presented to the Storting's larger division - the Odelsting. Such bills may concern new legislature, the amendment or the repeal of existing legislature. When handling legislative matters, the Storting splits in the Odelsting and the Lagting - the smaller division</p></td>
<td>
<h3>Reports to the Storting</h3>
<p>&nbsp;<strong>"Stortingsmeldinger (St.meld.)"<br /></strong>are reports being used by the Government to present matters to the Storting without inviting the Ting to pass legislative. fiscal or other resolutions. Such documents often report on activities in the past, or discuss future activities. Such reports, and their treatment in the Storting, often form the basis for future bills</p>
<p>&nbsp;<br /><strong>"Odelstingsmeldinger (Ot.meld.)"<br /></strong>are reports being used when the Government (rarely) wants to address the Odelsting without proposing amendments in existing legislature. A legislative bill which has been presented to the Odelsting, can e.g. be withdrawn by such a report to the Odelsting".</p></td></tr></tbody></table>&nbsp;<br />
  </div>
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
